        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 4 at 7:59PM EDT by NWS Cleveland OH</headline>
        <description>At 758 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Loudonville, or 14 miles south of Ashland, moving northwest at 35
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Mansfield, Ashland, Shelby, Ontario, Lexington, Crestline,
Loudonville, New London, Plymouth, New Washington, Hayesville,
Savannah, Greenwich, Perrysville, Lucas, Bailey Lakes, Tiro, Mifflin,
Mohicanville, and Nankin.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
